Quoted By:
>>52263785
For writing it really just depends on what the story itself needs and how long it's going to be. A short green text where the protag is explicitly a self insert? Nothing wrong with second person. A long form romance in prose? Probably going to be 1st or 3rd. A mystery with switching perspectives? Could be 1st or second. I've done a few longer stories in second where the protag isn't meant to be a self insert and after dabbling in 1st person for a while I've come to the conclusion that 1st is just a generally better POV for a character meant to have their own thoughts and opinions on things.

For reading all three are fine, I honestly haven't yet come across a story where I thought it could be done better with a different POV.
